name: 1920 CANADIAN GOVERNMENT F.3 AT SAULT STE MARIE AFTERING PASSING OVER NORTH BAY

desc.html: Image taken during arrival of the Canadian Government F.3 at Sault Ste. Marie during the first crossing of Canada by airplane. The F.3 was flown by Canadian Air Force pilots, who had overflown North Bay, using the town as a checkpoint to navigate their flight.
